#!/usr/bin/env python3
"""attio-ingest — pull Attio CRM data into ~/brain/{people,companies}/.

Marcus-only by default: ingests records where marcus@erv.io appears as
owner_member_id on last_email_interaction or last_calendar_interaction,
plus all records on the three qualifying named lists confirmed
2026-05-19: 'Top co fundraise', 'LP Fundraising', 'The Drop'.

Three passes:
  1. People + Companies — find-or-create entity pages, dedup by email
     local-part / domain, populate frontmatter, append a stub or net-new
     facts to ## Recent Activity.
  2. Notes — fetch all notes for every qualifying record (regardless
     of which team member authored them); dedup by attio-note:<id>
     citation already on the page; append to ## Timeline.
  3. Interaction metadata — project last_*_interaction.{interacted_at,
     owner_actor} into frontmatter (attio_first_contact, attio_last_contact,
     attio_interaction_count, attio_last_owner).

Delta sync: ~/bin/.last-attio-sync (ISO timestamp). On subsequent runs,
filter records by updated_at >= watermark; if Attio rejects that filter
slug, fall back to last_*_interaction.interacted_at >= watermark.
Watermark advances only after all writes succeed.

Auth: ATTIO_API_KEY in macOS keychain.
  security add-generic-password -a "$USER" -s ATTIO_API_KEY -w '<key>'
Scopes required (verified via /v2/self): record_permission:read,
object_configuration:read, note:read, list_configuration:read,
list_entry:read, user_management:read.

No LLM calls in default mode. --enrich-notes is reserved for a future
Haiku entity extraction pass (not implemented yet).

This script does not call brain-sync. brain-run --with-attio invokes
it as Phase 2.5 between Granola and Cal-mail.
"""
